"              \n              \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by Global Justice Center&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Given the rapidly changing environment in Burma, how should DFID’s programme develop?&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;Given the extraordinary opportunity Burma has to move towards democracy, is DFID’s programme giving sufficient attention to assisting this process? &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Are DFID’s plans to strengthen the work of Burma’s parliament adequate? Should DFID be doing more in this area?&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;What role should DFID play in helping to resolve ethnic tensions?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow effectively is DFID working with the FCO and other UK Government Departments, and how might this improve?&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;References&#xa0;\n \n“Poverty elimination and the empowerment of women; strategies for achieving the international development targets” DFID, Sept. 2000, at 8-9 [hereafter, “TSP”].\n \nTSP, at 8.\n \n “Empowerment: A journey not a destination,” Pathways of women’s empowerment (6 Jan. 2012), at 9 [hereafter “Pathways”]\n \n“Summary of DFID’s work in Burma 2011-2015, DFID, June 2013.\n Burma Operational Plan: Gender Annex, DFID, p. 2.\n \nPathways, at 9.\n \n“Summary of DFID’s work in Burma 2011-2015, DFID, June 2013.\nReuters, \nSuu\n \nKyi\n calls for speedy change to Myanmar constitution, Sept. 17, 2013, \nhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2013/09/17/us-myanmar-suukyi-idUSBRE98G0ZZ20130917\n Myanmar Const. at Ch VII, arts. \n340, 341 and 342.\n \nMyanmar Const. at Ch. XIV, art.\n \n445; Ch. 1, art.\n \n20(b), Ch. VII, art.\n 343.\n \nMyanmar Const. at Ch. III, art.\n \n71(b), Ch. IV, art.\n \n141(b).\n Myanmar Const. at \n Myanmar Constitution, \nat .\n \nMyanmar Constitution at Ch. 1, art.\n \n20(b), Ch. VII, art.\n 343.\n International Parliamentary Union, \nWomen in National Parliaments\n, available at: \nhttp://www.ipu.org/wmn-e/classif.htm\n (accessed